   - The one on the "left" diagonal (toward center on previous side)

   - The one on the "right" diagonal (toward center on next side)

   Actually, standard method from known hex spiral solutions:

   For a number on side s, position p in ring k:

   The six neighbors are:

   1. Previous on ring: if p > 1: n-1; else: last number of side s-1

   2. Next on ring: if p < k: n+1; else: first number of side s+1

   3. Inward: number on side s, position p in ring k-1

   4. Outward: number on side s, position p in ring k+1

   5. Left diagonal: number on side s-1, position p in ring k

   6. Right diagonal: number on side s+1, position p in ring k

